body:
@guozhangwang Thanks for reviewing, rebased and addressed your comments with following up unit test fixes.

For your two comments:

> 1) Move DefaultClientSupplier into streams/processor/internals as it does not need to be public interface.

Actually I was thinking below as the practical use since I'm expecting that in most cases only producer or consumer is the injection target. What do you think of?

``` java
KafkaStreams streams = new KafkaStreams(topology, config, new DefaultKafkaClientSupplier() {
    @Override
    public Producer<byte[], byte[]> getProducer(Map<String, Object> config) {
        return new MyKafkaProducer<>(...);
    }
});
```

> 2) Could you also create a MockClientSupplier which uses the MockProducer and MockConsumer and add a unit test to validate that the clients are generated as expected?

Ack. Addressed by: c2a5a5a and 8b13ced.

@ewencp console consumer may have been an oversight; updated
Ran sanity checks and a subset of tests here: https://jenkins.confluent.io/job/system-test-kafka-branch-builder-2/59/console
1. I definitely agree that there is quite a bit of fairly similar boilerplate between services, although I don't think this PR is the place for consolidation

@onurkaraman Excluding the map entry makes sense to me. Should we ensure this in `AbstractPartitionAssignor.assign` by only adding `numPartitions` to the map if it's not null and `> 0`? This probably works fine at the moment given the current implementation of `Cluster.partitionCountForTopics`, but it seems a bit brittle given that we have no tests for it. Alternatively, instead of coding defensively, we could add a test for `Cluster.partitionCountForTopics` to ensure the behaviour of `partitionCountForTopics` for this case.

What do you think @hachikuji @onurkaraman, is either of these options worth it or overkill? Part of the code for `AbstractPartitionAssignor.assign`:

``` java
        for (String topic : allSubscribedTopics) {
            Integer numPartitions = metadata.partitionCountForTopic(topic);
            if (numPartitions != null)
                partitionsPerTopic.put(topic, numPartitions);
            else
                log.debug("Skipping assignment for topic {} since no metadata is available", topic);
        } 
```

@Ishiihara - the very pessimistic check
"val segmentSize = segment.nextOffset() - segment.baseOffset"
is still present in this PR
